ated literature. The ERIC database corresponds to two printed journals: Resources in Education (RIE) and Current Index to Journals in Education (CIJE). Both journals provide access to some 14,000 documents and over 20,000 journal articles per year. The ERIC Database corresponds to two printed sources of indexing for published literature in the field of education.  Resources in Education (RIE) and Current Index to Journals in Education (CIJE).  It covers 14,000 documents and over 20,000 journal articles per year.  \r\n\r\nERIC documents (those listed with &quot;ED&quot; numbers) are available on microfiche in the Evansdale Library.\r\n\r\n',1245079133,1301664174,'eric',0,1301664174,0,0),(114,'GeoBase',1,'',48,'http://www.engineeringvillage.com/search/quick.url?CID=quickSearch&database=8192','','4',2,0,0,0,48,'Ask A Librarian','http://westvirginia.libanswers.com/','GEOBASE is a database of indexed research literature on the earth sciences, including geology, human and physical geography, environmental sciences, oceanography, geomechanics, alternative energy sources, pollution, waste management and nature conservation. Geobase covers thousands of peer-reviewed journals, trade publications, book series and conference proceedings',1245079133,1409149274,'geob',0,1409112000,0,0),(115,'Cochrane Library',1,'',16,'http://www.thecochranelibrary.com/view/0/index.html','','7',2,1,0,0,48,'Searching in Cochrane Library\r\n\r\n','http://www.cochranelibrary.com/help/how-to-use-cochrane-library.html','The Cochrane Library consists of a regularly updated collection of evidence-based medicine databases, including the Database of Systematic Reviews, the Database of Reviews of Effectiveness, and the Cochrane Central Register of Controlled Trials. \r\n\r\nPublished on a quarterly basis, it is designed to provide information and evidence to support decision-making in health care and to inform those who are receiving care.\r\n\r\n',1245079133,1423237563,'1138999625',0,1423237563,0,0),(478,'